{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SLm1ViBDuVv5swqQ1zfz8u","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Key findings:\n1. The `es-secure-settings` Secret contains the S3/MinIO credentials (`s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key`) - both are \"minioadmin\".\n2. The Secret is mounted at `/mnt/secure-settings` in each ES pod (read-only).\n3. The statefulset has `updateStrategy: type: OnDelete` - so rolling updates won't happen automatically.\n4. The s3 plugin is installed via an init container.\n5. The keystore is not yet initialized with the credentials.\n\nThe Elasticsearch S3 plugin requires credentials to be in the keystore, not in plain files. \n\nI need to load those mounted credentials into the keystore on each pod using the add-file command, then reload the secure settings API to apply them without restarting. After that, I can register the MinIO snapshot repository and create a snapshot. Let me check the elasticsearch.yml config to see how the S3 client is set up.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1391,"cache_read_input_tokens":30733,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1391},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c62977a3-ad28-43cf-bc55-0ff8fd1c2f4c","uuid":"55429310-8648-4df7-8069-2cc4e5d069bf","request_id":"req_011CbyD8e5ycdgXnhdnB82fm"}
