{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012Vny3dudXuawG9gWBX6So9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is complete. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**What was set up:**\n\n1. **Keystore credentials** — The Secret `es-secure-settings` had `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key` mounted at `/mnt/secure-settings/` on each pod. I added both values into the Elasticsearch keystore on all 3 nodes using `elasticsearch-keystore add --stdin`, reading from the mounted files (never from env vars or elasticsearch.yml).\n\n2. **Secure settings reload** — Called `POST /_nodes/reload_secure_settings` to activate the keystore credentials on all 3 nodes without a restart (all 3 reported successful).\n\n3. **Repository registration** — Registered `minio-repo` as an S3-type repository pointing to `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9000`, bucket `es-backups`, with `path_style_access: true` and `protocol: http`. Repository verification confirmed all 3 nodes can reach MinIO.\n\n4. **Snapshot** — Created `snapshot-1` with state `SUCCESS`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":359,"cache_read_input_tokens":42710,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":359},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c62977a3-ad28-43cf-bc55-0ff8fd1c2f4c","uuid":"8481d01b-74ea-40a6-89a6-2f5f7d6438f4","request_id":"req_011CbyDHYmzYE99ngs4oaQeN"}
